# V5 Transactions High-Fidelity Styling落落

Restore the Transactions grid to match the provided screenshot reference while maintaining the power of the Tabulator engine.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component] CSS Layer (system.css)
- Implement `.txn-grid-v5` theme:
  - Header: Purple background (`#9333ea`), white bold text.
  - Header Filters: White background inputs within the purple header row.
  - Border: Vertical separators between columns.
  - Rows: Alternate background or subtle borders.
- Add `.txn-badge` for source identifier pills (Blue/Teal).
- Refine `.desc-cell` for 1:1 occupancy with the reference.
- Update `.amount-negative` and `.amount-positive` to match the exact red/neutral colors in the screenshot.

### [Component] JavaScript Layer (app.js)
- Update [initGrid](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js#477-557) column definitions:
  - Order: `[Selection, Ref#, Date, Source, Description, Debit, Credit, Balance, Account]`
  - Add `headerFilter: "input"` to all searchable columns.
  - Implement [Source](file:///g:/My%20Drive/AutoBookkeeping/AutoBookkeeping-V4/src/pages/txn-import-v5-v2.js#2792-2803) formatter: Return a `<span class="txn-badge">TXN</span>`.
  - Refine [Description](file:///g:/My%20Drive/AutoBookkeeping/AutoBookkeeping-V4/src/pages/txn-import-v5-v2.js#5431-5433) formatter: Prepend selection dot (visual) if required, or keep standard selection column.
  - Ensure [Balance](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/types/coa.ts#57-58) column uses correct coloring logic for negative sums (Red/Bold).

